<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2472] The terms index divisor in IW should be set via IWC not via getReader</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2472</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;The getReader call gives a false sense of security... since if deletions have already been applied (and IW is pooling) the readers have already been loaded with a divisor of 1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Better to set the divisor up front in IWC.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
